  "text": "Hydralazine is a commonly prescribed antihypertensive medication that has been associated with both drug-induced lupus erythematosus and vasculitis. [CITATION_1] There is significant clinical, histopathologic, and serologic overlap between these entities. We present an unusual case of hydralazine-induced autoimmune syndrome with elements of both drug-induced lupus and vasculitis, as well as Sweet syndromeelike cutaneous lesions with distinctive histopathologic cryptococcoid inflammatory cells.",
